{"body": "\r\nThe benefit of strict sanitizing in test mode show itself when you have something more than CRUD and create models not only from forms but by assigning all attributes manually as well. \r\nLike create comment from email response and forget that `author_id` is protected from mass assingment.\r\n\r\n\r\nSo, You propose to include some sort of list of attribute names withing strict sanitizer that are ok \r\nAnd include `id` attribute in that list by default. Did I get you right?\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1580214", "created_at": "2011-07-15T14:45:20Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2067#issuecomment-1580214", "updated_at": "2011-07-15T14:45:20Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 2067, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/bogdan", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F926d19e70f74c20f796d376aafa3c6e2.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/received_events", "gravatar_id": "91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "bogdan", "type": "User", "id": 122436, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523848bdbd3543c1510111a3"}, "id": 1580214, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2067"}
